- "mature flowers" metaphorically refers to countries with the highest average monitoring years for their datasets;
- "verification journeys" refer to the history of dataset verifications, including initial and subsequent verifications;
- "garden of data" symbolizes the collection of datasets across different countries.

- 'golden apples' metaphorically refers to datasets that are of high quality and have been successfully completed;
- 'orchard of wisdom' represents the database where these datasets are stored;
- 'caretakers are scholars' indicates that the users who verified the datasets are researchers;
- 'years of the great enlightenment (1985-1995)' refers to the monitoring years between 1985 and 1995;
- 'ancient IHEB tree' symbolizes the data source IHEB;
- 'finest specimens (quality score > 8)' signifies datasets with a quality score greater than 8;
- 'digital form of JSON' specifies that the datasets are in JSON format.

- 'Top-quality dataset' refers to the dataset with the highest quality score within each country and format;
- 'Robust and valuable treasure chest' is a metaphor for a country with a high average dataset size for its top-quality datasets;
- 'Largest average size' refers to the average size of datasets in bytes.

- 'Garden of Europe' refers to countries in the European region;
- 'Dawn of 1980' and 'Twilight of 1990' refer to the years 1980 and 1990, respectively;
- 'Score shines brighter than 8' means the average quality score is greater than 8.

- "Verified" means the dataset has been checked and approved by a user with the appropriate permissions;
- "Permissions" refer to the roles and access levels assigned to users who have verified the datasets;
- "Country distribution" indicates the number of datasets per country, reflecting the geographic spread of data collection.

- 'IHEB' stands for 'Institute of Higher Education and Beyond', a reputable data source;
- 'External agency' refers to other data sources outside of IHEB;
- The average data size and quality are calculated across all datasets in the database.

- "Blossoming garden" refers to a country with datasets;
- "Nurturing at least one dataset that is yet to bloom" refers to having pending datasets (status_id = 1);
- "Holding more than one flower in its plot for a specific year" refers to having more than one dataset in a monitoring year;
- "Average beauty (quality score) is above 8" refers to an average quality score greater than 8.

- 'European countries' refers to countries in the region of Europe;
- 'High quality score' typically means a score greater than 8;
- 'Monitored in the 1980s' refers to the monitoring years between 1980 and 1990;
- 'Multiple entries' means more than one dataset per group.

- "bloomed with more than the average number of datasets" refers to the total number of datasets being greater than the average number of datasets across all countries;
- "average quality score that surpasses the overall average" means the average quality score for the country is higher than the average quality score across all datasets;
- "after the midpoint of the monitoring years" indicates that only datasets from years later than the average monitoring year are considered.

- "Completed" refers to datasets that have been fully processed and are ready for use;
- "Monitoring year" indicates the year in which the data collection or monitoring was conducted;
- "Average dataset size" is calculated by taking the mean of the data sizes of all datasets in the database.

- 'Proud guardians' refers to countries;
- 'Thriving collection' refers to multiple datasets;
- 'Completed datasets' are datasets with a status of 'Completed';
- 'More than a mere speck of data' refers to datasets larger than 100,000 bytes;
- 'Substantial repository' refers to the total data size of more than 1,000,000 bytes;
- 'Data hoard' refers to the total data size of the datasets.

- 'status_id = 0' refers to datasets that are in the initial or draft stage;
- 'Average_Quality_Score' is the mean quality score of datasets for each country;
- 'global average' is the mean quality score of all datasets in the database.

- "European countries" refers to countries in the region of Europe;
- "Geographical extent" refers to the range of latitude and longitude values;
- "Data analysts" are users with the role of data analyst;
- "Total data size" is the sum of the sizes of datasets in bytes;
- "Average quality score" is the mean quality score of datasets.
